&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Italy.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Italy&lt;/strong&gt; has passed a historic law recognising &lt;strong&gt;femicide&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;mdash;the gender-motivated killing of women&amp;mdash;as a separate crime punishable with &lt;strong&gt;life imprisonment&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The law formally defines &lt;strong&gt;femicide&lt;/strong&gt; as the intentional killing of women due to their gender, often rooted in misogyny and patriarchal control.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Italy classifies femicide under &lt;strong&gt;three categories&lt;/strong&gt;: partner-related, family-related, and non-family perpetrators.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Recognising femicide separately helps generate &lt;strong&gt;accurate national statistics&lt;/strong&gt; for targeted policymaking.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The legislation aims to strengthen understanding of &lt;strong&gt;gendered violence, toxic masculinity&lt;/strong&gt; and patterns preceding gender-based killings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meaning of Femicide&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Defined as the killing of women precisely because they are women.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;litypically and=&quot;&quot; by=&quot;&quot; control=&quot;&quot; driven=&quot;&quot; family=&quot;&quot; intimate=&quot;&quot; involves=&quot;&quot; li=&quot;&quot; men=&quot;&quot; or=&quot;&quot; power=&quot;&quot;&gt; &lt;/litypically&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Recognition Matters&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Identifies gendered motives behind severe violence against women.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Helps law enforcement track patterns of harassment, coercion and escalation.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Aids in shaping prevention strategies and victim protection systems.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Categories Recognised Under the Law&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partner-related&lt;/strong&gt; femicide (most common globally).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Family-related&lt;/strong&gt; femicide involving household or relatives.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Non-family perpetrators&lt;/strong&gt; including acquaintances or strangers.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Social Significance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Promotes awareness of &lt;strong&gt;misogyny, harassment and control-driven violence&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Highlights need for early interventions and counselling for at-risk individuals.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;listrengthens by=&quot;&quot; crimes=&quot;&quot; for=&quot;&quot; gender=&quot;&quot; justice=&quot;&quot; li=&quot;&quot; showing=&quot;&quot; targeting=&quot;&quot; tolerance=&quot;&quot; zero=&quot;&quot;&gt; &lt;/listrengthens&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Presidential Awards&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Sangeet Natak Academy Awards&lt;/strong&gt; were earlier known as the &lt;strong&gt;Presidential Awards&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;These awards are given to artists in the field of performing arts such as music, dance, and drama.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The awards aim to recognize and honor the outstanding contribution of artists to Indian cultural heritage.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Established in 1952, the Sangeet Natak Academy is India&amp;#39;s national academy for music, dance, and drama.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Sangeet Natak Academy&lt;/strong&gt; functions as an autonomous organization under the Ministry of Culture, Government of India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It not only honors artists but also engages in various activities to promote and preserve the rich cultural heritage of India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The awards are conferred by the President of India, which adds to their prestige and recognition.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Recipients of the awards receive a plaque, a shawl, and a cash prize.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is the &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Transitions command&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In MS-PowerPoint, slide show options available to the presenter include all of the following, except for the &lt;strong&gt;Transitions command&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Slide transitions&lt;/strong&gt; are the animation effects that are applied to whole-slide when one by one next slide is displayed during a presentation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Speaker notes&lt;/strong&gt; in PowerPoint are the&amp;nbsp;essential part of a presentation, they&amp;nbsp;help presenters recall important points, such as stats&amp;nbsp;or key messages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ctrl+N&lt;/strong&gt; is the shortcut key in MS Powerpoint that opens a new blank slide in another window of the Powerpoint program.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Microsoft PowerPoint&lt;/strong&gt; is a slide show presentation program created by&lt;strong&gt; Robert Gaskins&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Dennis Austin&lt;/strong&gt; in &lt;strong&gt;1987&lt;/strong&gt;. Slides are used by MS PowerPoint to convey information rich in multimedia.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The current CEO of Microsoft Corporation is &lt;strong&gt;Mr.Satya Nadella&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Satya Nadella is the CEO of Microsoft since &lt;strong&gt;2014.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

