&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;The President approved a total of &lt;strong&gt;301 military decorations&lt;/strong&gt; to Armed Forces and other personnel.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ati Vishisht Seva Medal (AVSM):&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;56 awards&lt;/strong&gt; were approved for distinguished service of an exceptional order.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Param Vishisht Seva Medal (PVSM):&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;30 awards&lt;/strong&gt; were approved for distinguished service of the most exceptional order.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;Prominent PVSM awardees include Lt Gen Jagmohan Singh Sidana, Vice Adm Krishna Swaminathan, and Air Mshl Ashutosh Dixit.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Other Distinguished Service Awards (2026)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Uttam Yudh Seva Medal (UYSM):&lt;/strong&gt; 4&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Yudh Seva Medal (YSM):&lt;/strong&gt; 9&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vishisht Seva Medal (VSM):&lt;/strong&gt; 135&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sena Medal (Distinguished):&lt;/strong&gt; 43&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct option is (2)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tape drive&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Nonvolatile mass storage devices called &amp;quot;block devices&amp;quot; provide access to data in any order. Block devices include things like CD-ROMs, floppy discs, and hard drives.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;For backup and archiving reasons, a tape drive is a device that stores computer data on magnetic tape.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;To back up and recover data, tape drives are always utilized. Despite being much less common than disc drives, tape drives serve a crucial purpose.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Mouse:-&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;A hand-held pointing device called a computer mouse (plural mice, occasionally mice) senses two-dimensional motion in relation to a surface.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;USB port:-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;The USB-A connector can charge devices like smartphones and other electronics in addition to connecting USB drives, keyboards, and mice.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Keyboard:-&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Using a keyboard, you can input letters, words, and numbers into your computer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sushira Vadya&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sushira Vadya&lt;/strong&gt; refers to wind instruments where sound is produced by blowing air into a hollow column.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Common examples of Sushira Vadya include the flute, shehnai, and harmonium.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The vibration of air within the hollow tube creates sound, and the pitch can be varied by changing the length of the air column.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;These instruments are categorized under the ancient Indian classification of musical instruments based on how sound is produced.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sushira Vadya is distinct from other categories like Tata Vadya (string instruments) or Avanaddha Vadya (percussion instruments).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Classification of Indian Musical Instruments:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Indian instruments are traditionally classified into four types: Tata Vadya (string instruments), Avanaddha Vadya (percussion instruments), Sushira Vadya (wind instruments), and Ghana Vadya (solid instruments).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mechanism of Sound Production:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;In Sushira Vadya, air vibrations caused by blowing into the instrument generate sound waves within the hollow column.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The frequency of these waves determines the pitch, which can be manipulated using finger holes or valves.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Examples of Sushira Vadya:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Traditional instruments: Flute, Shehnai, Nadaswaram.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Modern instruments: Clarinet, Saxophone.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role in Indian Music:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Sushira Vadya plays a vital role in both classical and folk music traditions.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;These instruments are often used for melody and accompaniment.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goa&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goa&lt;/strong&gt; recorded the &lt;strong&gt;highest Scheduled Tribes (ST) sex ratio&lt;/strong&gt; in 2011 according to the Census of India data.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The ST sex ratio in Goa was &lt;strong&gt;1,046 females per 1,000 males&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Goa is known for having a relatively smaller percentage of the &lt;strong&gt;Scheduled Tribes&lt;/strong&gt; population in comparison to other Indian states.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The high ST sex ratio is an indicator of &lt;strong&gt;gender parity&lt;/strong&gt; among tribal communities in Goa.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The state has seen a growth in the tribal population in recent decades, with a focus on &lt;strong&gt;preserving cultural heritage&lt;/strong&gt; and improving education and healthcare facilities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Goa has a mixed population with influences from &lt;strong&gt;Portuguese colonial history&lt;/strong&gt; and indigenous tribal communities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The tribal groups in Goa include the &lt;strong&gt;Gawdas&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Kunbis&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;Velips&lt;/strong&gt;, among others.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mizoram&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Mizoram had a high ST sex ratio of &lt;strong&gt;1,007 females per 1,000 males&lt;/strong&gt;, but it was not the highest.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The state is home to various tribes, such as the &lt;strong&gt;Lusei, Hmar, and Chakma&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Mizoram has a well-developed education system that contributes to the strong position of women in tribal communities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Arunachal Pradesh&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Arunachal Pradesh recorded a ST sex ratio of &lt;strong&gt;1,032 females per 1,000 males&lt;/strong&gt;, higher than Goa, but not the highest.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The state is home to diverse tribal groups, including the &lt;strong&gt;Apatanis, Nyishis, and Mishmis&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Gender equality and a strong focus on education have positively influenced the ST sex ratio in Arunachal Pradesh.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tamil Nadu&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Tamil Nadu recorded a lower ST sex ratio of &lt;strong&gt;981 females per 1,000 males&lt;/strong&gt; in 2011 compared to Goa and other states.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The state has a large population of &lt;strong&gt;Scheduled Castes (SC)&lt;/strong&gt; and a significant number of &lt;strong&gt;Scheduled Tribes (ST)&lt;/strong&gt; mainly in hilly areas.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Improved access to education and healthcare has contributed to the betterment of tribal populations in Tamil Nadu.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Egypt.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;India and Egypt are conducting the joint military exercise &amp;#39;Cyclone 2025&amp;#39; at the Mahajan Field Firing Range in Rajasthan.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;Cyclone 2025&amp;#39; is the third edition of the exercise between India and Egypt.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The exercise focuses on enhancing defence cooperation and interoperability between the two countries&amp;#39; special forces in desert environments.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It includes various counter-terrorism operations, reconnaissance, raids, and specialized missions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Personnel from India&amp;#39;s Parachute Regiment and Egypt&amp;#39;s Commando Squadron and Airborne Platoon are participating.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Cyclone Exercise&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A joint military exercise conducted by India and Egypt to strengthen defence ties&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Aims to enhance interoperability and share professional skills between the countries&amp;#39; armed forces&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Involves specialized missions such as counter-terrorism, reconnaissance, and raids&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;India-Egypt Military Cooperation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The partnership between India and Egypt has been strengthened in recent years through joint exercises and collaborations&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Emphasis on enhancing security efforts and mutual defence interests&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Parachute Regiment&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Specialized unit of the Indian Army involved in airborne operations&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Highly skilled in operations such as combat free-fall, reconnaissance, and surveillance&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mahatma Gandhi&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Mahatma Gandhi launched the Non-cooperation Movement in 1920 as a response to the Jallianwala Bagh massacre and the Rowlatt Act.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The movement aimed to resist British rule in India through non-violent means or &amp;quot;Ahimsa&amp;quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It was a mass protest against the British government&amp;#39;s oppressive policies and aimed to attain self-governance or Swaraj.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Gandhi urged people to withdraw their children from government schools, boycott British goods, resign from government employment, and refuse to pay taxes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Jallianwala Bagh Massacre:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A tragic incident that took place on April 13, 1919, in Amritsar, where British troops fired on a large crowd of unarmed Indian protesters, causing hundreds of deaths.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This event marked a turning point in Indian nationalism and galvanized the Indian population against British rule.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rowlatt Act:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;An oppressive legislation passed by the British government in 1919 giving them the power to imprison any person suspected of terrorism without trial for up to two years.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The act faced widespread opposition and was one of the catalysts for the Non-cooperation Movement.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Swaraj:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A term used to describe self-governance or &amp;quot;self-rule,&amp;quot; which was the ultimate goal of the Indian independence movement.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Gandhi&amp;#39;s vision of Swaraj included not just political independence but also social and economic empowerment of the common people.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ahimsa:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A principle of non-violence which is central to Gandhi&amp;#39;s philosophy and strategy for the independence movement.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Gandhi believed that non-violence was the most powerful weapon for oppressed people to achieve freedom and justice.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

questions.statement:
How many rural households were graded based on deprivation criteria, as per Socio&lt;br /&gt;
Economic and Caste Census (SECC) that was concluded by the Ministry of Rural&lt;br /&gt;
Development in March, 2016?

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;8.72 crore&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;As per the Socio-Economic and Caste Census (SECC) conducted by the Ministry of Rural Development, &lt;strong&gt;8.72 crore rural households&lt;/strong&gt; were graded based on deprivation criteria.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The SECC was a significant initiative aimed at identifying households based on &lt;strong&gt;economic and social deprivation parameters&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This census was concluded in &lt;strong&gt;March 2016&lt;/strong&gt; and formed the basis for targeting beneficiaries under various social welfare schemes.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The SECC categorization ensures &lt;strong&gt;better targeting of subsidies and welfare programs&lt;/strong&gt; by identifying the most deprived households.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Socio-Economic and Caste Census (SECC):&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The SECC was conducted in 2011, with its analysis completed later for targeted policy implementation.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It aimed to collect data on multiple deprivation indicators such as housing, education level, income, and employment status.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deprivation Criteria:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Households were evaluated on factors such as income, land ownership, access to education, and type of dwelling.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;These criteria were used to prioritize households for government schemes like housing, employment, and healthcare.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Importance:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The SECC data is crucial for implementing targeted welfare policies for rural development.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It provides valuable insights into poverty and socio-economic challenges in India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ministry of Rural Development:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Ministry spearheaded the SECC initiative and ensured data collection from all rural households.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is responsible for implementing rural welfare programs in India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

