&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;The new drone warfare force of the Indian Army is named Bhairav.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Each Bhairav battalion is fully trained in advanced drone operations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;The force will comprise over one lakh trained drone operatives, among the largest globally.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Bhairav Force&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt; &lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Drone-centric modern combat unit&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Capable of surveillance, reconnaissance and precision strikes&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Designed for high-intensity, technology-driven warfare&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Bhairav Battalions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Function as agile, Special Forces&amp;ndash;like combat units&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Support frontline troops with drone-enabled firepower&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Bridge the operational gap between Para SF and Infantry battalions&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Deployment and Expansion&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;15 Bhairav battalions already raised&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Deployed along both borders&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Plan to raise around 25 battalions in the near future&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Indian Army Modernisation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Focus on drone warfare and multi-domain operations&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Lessons drawn from recent global conflicts&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Transition towards technology-led battlefield dominance&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Raj Kumar Goyal.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Raj Kumar Goyal has been sworn in as the Chief Information Commissioner of India at Rashtrapati Bhavan, with President Droupadi Murmu administering the oath.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goyal is a retired 1990-batch IAS officer of the AGMUT cadre and has previously served as Secretary in the Ministry of Law and Justice and Home Ministry.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;His appointment was recommended by a three-member committee headed by Prime Minister Narendra Modi.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The CIC post had been vacant since former CIC Heeralal Samariya demitted office in September 2025.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;With his appointment, the Central Information Commission regains leadership and is expected to return to near full strength with new Information Commissioners.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Central Information Commission (CIC)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A statutory body established under the Right to Information Act, 2005, to address complaints from individuals unable to obtain information from public authorities.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Comprises one Chief Information Commissioner and up to ten Information Commissioners, appointed by the President on the recommendation of a committee.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Oath of Office&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The oath to the CIC is administered by the President of India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;President Droupadi Murmu administered the oath to Raj Kumar Goyal.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Past Women CICs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Deepak Sandhu (fourth CIC overall) and Sushma Singh (fifth CIC overall) have served as Chief Information Commissioners.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Significance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Ensures smooth functioning of the Central Information Commission.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Strengthens transparency and accountability under the Right to Information Act.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S.P. Sharma.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S.P. Sharma is the author of the book &amp;quot;India@2047: Charts Roadmap to Global Economic Leadership.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The book discusses India&amp;#39;s rise as a resilient economy with 8%+ growth and highlights transformative initiatives like Make in India and digital innovation.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The author of the book &lt;u&gt;&amp;quot;India@2047: Charts Roadmap to Global Economic Leadership&amp;quot;&lt;/u&gt; is &lt;u&gt;S.P. Sharma&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The book outlines India&amp;#39;s future as a resilient, reform-driven economy with sustained 8%+ growth.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It emphasizes key initiatives like Make in India, IMEC, and digital innovation that are seen as crucial growth catalysts for India.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);  &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;S.P. Sharma&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Economist and author, known for his writings on India&amp;#39;s economic policies and growth trajectory.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;India@2047&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A vision for India&amp;#39;s economic leadership by the time it completes 100 years of independence in 2047.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
